datamap-mapsrcinfo-status-errors:
{{Doc-screenshot|DataMaps Source code page notice with errors.png}}
Message shown in a box instead of the map, only on source code pages (that is, not in articles). It indicates fatal errors with the map's source code (it does not pass data validation), and requires the errors to be fixed before the map can be displayed again.

This message is immediately followed by message {{msg-mw|datamap-mapsrcinfo-heading-errors}} on the next line, with a list of the errors. Optionally, {{msg-mw|datamap-mapsrcinfo-heading-warnings}} may also be shown below if any warnings had been raised during validation.
